*Title:* Enhancing Student Employability in Collaboration with the Industry: Case Study of a Partnership with Amazon Web Services Academy

*Summary:*

The article by Goteng, Shohel, and Tarig explores how universities can enhance student employability through collaboration with industries. Specifically, it examines a partnership between a university and Amazon Web Services (AWS) Academy. By incorporating industry-based practical hands-on labs into the curriculum, the study finds that students become more engaged and better prepared for immediate employment after graduation. This approach ensures that students acquire both theoretical knowledge and practical skills necessary for careers in cloud computing.

*Simple Correct Answer:*

The article discusses how partnering with AWS Academy can improve students' job readiness by combining theoretical learning with practical industry experience.
